# PH-ML work-package scope

## Branch rule

- One **WP-* ID** per feature branch (e.g. `feat/wp-ml-04-mnist-forward`).
- Wave sweeps (`feat/ph-ml-gpu-swarm`) are steward-only; agents resume with a single WP after merge.

## File-lock matrix

| Path | Steward | Parallel? |
|------|---------|-----------|
| `packages/li-ml/**`, `packages/li-ml-rl/**` | ML agent | Yes (different subdirs) |
| `packages/lig/**` | HW agent | One agent per batch |
| `compiler/mir/**`, `compiler/codegen/**` | Compiler agent | **Serial** — one agent at a time |
| `benchmarks/**` | Bench agent | Med — coordinate in tracker |

## Minimal touch

- Do not refactor unrelated packages, stdlib, or studio while landing a WP.
- Product logic stays in `.li` (`li-native-li-only`); vendor strings only at `runtime/**` + PH-HW gates.
- Update only the tracker row(s) for WPs you close; link release note when user-visible.

## Exit before PR

1. `./scripts/build.sh`
2. `lic check` on touched smokes
3. Tracker row: `state=done`, `verify=` command output summary
4. No honesty violations (`ph-ml-gpu-honesty.mdc`)
